{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2016}} {{infobox WorldScouting | type = event | name = Klondike derby | image = Klondike-Derby der Boy Scouts of America, Garmisch, 1984.jpg | imagesize = 260px | caption = The Klondike derby of the BSA Transatlantic Council at Germany, 1984 near [[Garmisch-Partenkirchen]]: [[German Scouts]] of the [[Deutsche Pfadfinderschaft Sankt Georg]]. | country=[[United States]], [[Canada]] | f-date = Winter | owner = [[Boy Scouts of America]] }} A '''Klondike derby''' is an annual event held by some [[Boy Scouts of America]] and [[Scouts Canada]] districts during the winter months and is based on the heritage of the [[Klondike Gold Rush]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scoutdocs.ca/Klondike/|title=Klondike, Ho!|accessdate=October 9, 2007|author=Morland, Liam|work=Scoutdocs }}</ref> BSA units have been running Klondike derbies since 1949.<ref>{{cite journal|title=The Grandaddy of Klondike Derbies|journal=Scouting|author=Peterson, Robert|issue=January–February 1999|url=http://www.scoutingmagazine.org/issues/9901/a-klon.html|accessdate=October 9, 2007 }}</ref>
The event varies by district, but the typical Klondike derby consists of several stations where patrols/units must test their [[Scoutcraft]] skills and their leadership abilities, earning points towards a total score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boyslife.org/outdoors/outdoorarticles/2638/plan-and-run-a-klondike-derby/|date=November 2007|title=Plan and Run a Klondike Derby|author=Derr, Aaron|accessdate=October 7, 2010|work=Boys' Life }}</ref> Often, one or more races are included while the Scouts navigate between stations.
The unit must transport their gear on a homemade sled pulled by the Scouts. Districts may have specific guidelines for the construction of sleds.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scoutingmagazine.org/about/download/klondike.pdf |title=Plans for Klondike Derby Sled (Sledge) |accessdate=October 9, 2007 |work=Scouting |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070125234912/http://www.scoutingmagazine.org/about/download/klondike.pdf |archivedate=January 25, 2007 |df= }}</ref>
== Variations== ''Extreme Klondike!'' is a front-country, up-to-24-hour, cold-weather, personal and team challenge for older Scouts and Venturers often held in conjunction with Klondike Derby. The aim of this variation is to increase/sustain older youth participation. Part backpacking, part survival, and/or part winter camping, the mini-High-Adventure ''Extreme Klondike!'' collection of events aims to replicate trail life in the Great Northwest by presenting a wide range of basic-skill, higher-standard challenges and letting the '[http://www.boyledtroop.org/index.php?title=Main_Page boy-led]' team decide who, when and how to complete each event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tecumsehcouncilbsa.org/Chillicothe/Events/CHLKlondikeDerbyShipWreckedinAlaska|title=Chillicothe Klondike Derby 'Ship Wrecked in Alaska'|publisher=[[Tecumseh Council]]|year=2016|accessdate=February 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecrater.com/p/23363300/n-12762-cac-pioneer-district-winter-camporee-2010|title=N-12762 CAC Pioneer District Winter Camporee 2010 Extreme Klondike Camp Belzer|publisher=[[eCRATER]]|date=September 19, 2015|accessdate=February 6, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://storage.scoutingvermont.org/event/docs/5914/three_rivers_2014_klondike_derby_registration_information_and_form.pdf |title=Three Rivers District Klondike Derby |publisher=[[Green Mountain Council]] |year=2014 |accessdate=February 6, 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128014715/http://storage.scoutingvermont.org/event/docs/5914/three_rivers_2014_klondike_derby_registration_information_and_form.pdf |archivedate=January 28, 2016 |df= }}</ref>
